node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Recovery and Resilience
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. Being able to recognize one of these wounds, and using positive language when discussing it, supports a positive culture across the Department of the Air Force and could save a life. It is important for Airmen and Guardians to seek help for invisible wounds, taking that first step towards recovery.
.
This video describes the importance of Airmen and Guardians seeking help for invisible wounds and how taking that first step towards recovery results in positive outcomes and enhanced resilience.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources
.
Over the past five years, United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has implemented solutions that drive timely, proactive case handling, equitable, informed interactions and decisions, engaged leadership and a supportive environment, and accessible, effective care delivery. 
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. The impact of invisible wounds and can develop at any time, in any place, in or out of uniform.
.
Learn more at: https://go.usa.gov/xszpN
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Signs and Symptoms
.
Since its inception in 2016, the United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has been a leader in creating a supportive culture for #Airmen living with invisible wounds. Being able to recognize an invisible wound could save a life. Airman can learn to see the signs and symptoms of invisible wounds in others that they may see in themselves.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. Charles Q. Brown, Jr., & @cmsaf_official discuss how empowering Airmen will lead to success in building the future Air Force today. They also discussed Accelerate Change or Lose, the Action Orders, leadership and followership, how to rise above bias & self-limitations, and the future of the #AirForce.
.
The primary focus of this call was to connect with Airmen across the world, and give insight to how the Action orders, new Air Force missions statement and developmental guidance are being implemented for the Total Force.
.
#RealTalk #CoffeeTalk #Future #Empowerment #Questions

node.text:
Nine C-17 Globemaster IIIs arrived in Kabul, Afghanistan recently delivering equipment and approximately 1000 troops. Seven flights departed, transporting approximately 700-800 passengers, 165 of which were American citizens.

This photo is not related to the crew that faced a security breach on the runway. Evacuations in Afghanistan are ongoing.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 15, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, aircraft and road.

node.text:
POV: You're losing tug-of-war 
.
Airmen from the 26th Expeditionary Rescue Squadron set up a Forward Area Refueling Point (FARP) for two F-15E Strike Eagles at an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia. FARP training prepares Airmen to effectively refuel aircraft in austere locations when air-to-air refueling is not possible or when fueling stations are not accessible. 
.
📸 by SrA Karla Parra
.
#militaryphotography #USAF #deployment

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, aircraft and sky.

node.text:
Look, Airman. Everything the light touches is our area of responsibility.
.
Senior Airmen John Klingenberger and Donny Arseneaux, loadmasters with the 53rd Weather Reconnaissance Squadron, sit on the ramp of a WC-130 during a buoy drop mission over the Gulf of Mexico.
.
The mission supported the U.S. Naval Academy oceanography department's Training and Research in Oceanic and Atmospheric Processes in Tropical Cyclones internship program.
.
📸 & caption by @af_reserve_hurricane_hunters
.
#hurricanehunters #militaryphotography #WC130

node.text:
General CQ Brown, Jr. was named an Honorary Tuskegee Airman and presented the Tuskegee Airman Red Jacket during a ceremony at the #AirForce memorial today.
.
This honorary membership has been a part of Tuskegee Airmen, Inc. National Office since the organization was formed in 1975. It is bestowed on an individual by the TAI Board in recognition of significant contributions in our society and/or in fostering goals of the organization.
.
#TuskegeeAirmen #Heritage @tainational

node.text:
Smokey, spooky vibes for #fridaythe13th
.
An Airman assigned to the 8th Civil Engineer Squadron shovels dirt and concrete during Rapid Airfield Damage Repair training at @KunsanAirBase, Republic of Korea. RADR is a multi-staged process which quickly and effectively repairs airfields, allowing for operations to continue in combat situations.
.
📸 Staff Sgt. Gabrielle Spalding
.
#militaryphotography #USAF
